CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1973, pg. 5, reads: "Liberate Africa - Pittsburghers joined nearly 100,000 demonstrators throughout this country and the western hemisphere in raising $37,000 for African Liberation groups fighting in colonial Africa. Gathered at a press conference during African Liberation Week here are, left to right, Ewari Ellis, Hill Cultural House; Roland Hayes, Model Cities-Hill District; Sala Udin Saif Salaam, Congress of Afrikan People; Jitu Weusi, The EAST, New York City; and Rev. Rosamund Kay, Morningstar Baptist Church, Clairton."
TitMainTitle: Men at press conference, from left: Ewari "Ed" Ellis, Roland Hayes, Sala Udin Saif Salaam (Sam Howze), Jitu Weusi, and Rev. Rosamund Kay, with Tim Stevens and Father August "Gus" Taylor seated in back, during African Liberation Week
